Greg Kroah-Hartman has been building the Linux kernel since 1996 and
started writing Linux kernel drivers in 1999.  He is currently the
maintainer of the USB, PCI, driver core and sysfs subsystems in the kernel
source tree and is also one half of the -stable kernel release team.  He
created the udev program and maintains the Linux hotplug userspace project.
He is a Gentoo Linux developer as well as the co-author of the third
edition of the <literal>Linux Device Drivers</literal> book and a
contributing editor to <literal>Linux Journal</literal> magazine.  He also
created and maintains the <literal>Linux Device Driver Kit</literal>.  He
currently works for SuSE Labs / Novell, doing various Linux kernel related
tasks.
